salmon /ˈsæmən/

(salmon) 

1. N-COUNT A salmon is a large silver-coloured fish. 三文鱼 

2. N-UNCOUNT Salmon is the orangey-pink flesh of this fish which is eaten as food. It is often smoked and eaten raw. 鲑鱼肉 

例： He gave them a splendid lunch of smoked salmon. 他款待了他们一顿极好的熏三文鱼午餐。

